title: Grateful Dead Live at Autzen Stadium, U. of Oregon on 1990-06-24
description: Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Loose Lucy, A Little Light, Picasso Moon, Candyman, Let It Grow Foolish Heart, Women Are Smarter, Standing On the Moon, Box Of Rain*, Estimated Prophet-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Jam-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: DL Links The downloading links for this show are not working.  Just a heads up.

Very fine audience quality-great set list! WhY someone (ie the previous reveiwer) would give a show 3 STARS just because the download links didn't work is asolutely dumb. 

Ok, this show is actually a 5 stars and for those of us with any basic computer knowledge guess what?- the links work and I now have a kind 5 star audience quality show. Thank God I only trust my own ear...

Greta hSF and the first set really is quite interesting. Set Two is a total jam fest. 

The sound tome anyway, sounds sort of flat but also someone seems to have 'dressed up' this tape quality in some aertificial way...sounds great to me! Clear vocals, all intruments are normalized (none superceed the other) and the crowd noise is almost non existant except between songs. 

Enjoy!

Not one of those magical spring 90's Jerry struggles out of the gate.  His voice is out on this show and there's just no denying that.  It hurts to listen to "Help."  Brent's song is okay, as are 'Picasso Moon" and "Let it Grow."  The latter might be the highlight of the show, but is not spectacular.  

Can't hear too much audience either, if you like that in an "aud"

Instead, its a MAGICAL SUMMER show One man gathers, what another man spills.........  SPRING is over and the boys are still kickin, out the jams.  This show is another great addition to the rest of the Eugene 1990 shows--OUTSTANDING. Do not be fooled!!! Never heard or knew otherwise over the last 17 years?!! Take that last review w/ a grain of salt--do not cheat yourself out of a great audience recording and show.  The first half of that 2nd set is a GIANT!!!!!!!!!    The band played w/ different intensitiy on each respective Coast--Eugene is not going to sound like a hyper-intense East coast show---it is Eugene--it is not a hyper-intense place or tribe of people.  In the rush to endless, convenient downloads--I guess the magic gets lost for some folks!  Too bad!  If you only had Maxells for the majority of your life--this shit is GOLD!!!
Titles are all mixed up Song titles are all mixed up - you need to fix them after unzipping -- enjoy ya'all zippa heads....

Grateful Dead Live at Autzen Fun times were had by many, GD rolling off the artificial turf, and thundered out yonder across the stadium bleacher seated Deadheads. The parking lot was spectacular, it was reported the local law enforcement gave out tickets out of Eugene towards Tacoma. Highly' rated!
